# Chat-P10 Delete All Sessions — Implementation Plan


## Implementation Audit (Current State)

| # | Task | Status | Evidence |
|---|------|--------|----------|
| 1 | Backend `delete_all_sessions()` in session.rs | ✅ DONE | Function at `backend/src/runtime/session.rs:88-127`, returns `DeleteAllResult { deleted_count, new_session_id }` |
| 2 | Backend route `DELETE /api/forge/chats/sessions` | ✅ DONE | Registered in `backend/src/forge/mod.rs` routes(): `.route("/api/forge/chats/sessions", get(..).delete(handlers::delete_all_forge_sessions))` |
| 3 | Frontend `deleteAllSessions()` in useSessions.ts | ✅ DONE | Function calls `DELETE ${API_BASE}/sessions`, parses response, replaces `_sessionList` with new session |
| 4 | Frontend delete-all button in ChatsView.vue | ✅ DONE | Trash2 icon button in sidebar header (line ~12), hidden when `sessionList.length === 0` |
| 5 | Frontend confirmation flow | ✅ DONE (basic) | Uses native `confirm(t('chat.confirmDeleteAll'))` — no ConfirmDialog component |
| 6 | i18n keys | ✅ DONE | `chat.deleteAllSessions`, `chat.confirmDeleteAll` exist in en.json/zh.json |
| 7 | Backend tests | ✅ DONE | 6 inline tests in session.rs pass (delete_all, create_dir_if_missing, empty_dir, etc.) |
| 8 | Frontend tests | ✅ DONE | 5 tests in useSessions.spec.ts pass (success, network error, 500, hasSessions) |

## Remaining Work — Upgrade Confirmation Dialog

The current implementation uses the browser's native `confirm()` dialog. Chat-D1 specifies a styled `ConfirmDialog` component with session count display, loading state, and retry capability. `ConfirmDialog.vue` does **not** exist yet.

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P10.1 | Create `ConfirmDialog.vue` component | Coder | 1.5h | — | draft | Create `frontend/src/components/ConfirmDialog.vue` as a generic modal dialog. Props: `open: boolean`, `title: string`, `message: string`, `confirmText: string`, `cancelText: string`, `loading: boolean`, `variant: 'danger' \| 'default'`. Emits: `confirm`, `cancel`. Template: overlay backdrop → centered dialog card → title row (with ⚠️ icon for danger variant) → message body → button row (Cancel gray, Confirm red for danger). Slots for custom body content. Transitions: fade backdrop + slide-down dialog. **Files:** create `frontend/src/components/ConfirmDialog.vue` **Deliverable:** component renders; props control visibility/content; emits fire on click/Escape; `role="alertdialog"` + `aria-modal="true"` for accessibility. per Chat-D1 §ConfirmDeleteDialog |
| P10.2 | Replace native `confirm()` in ChatsView.vue | Coder | 1h | P10.1 | draft | Remove `confirm()` call from `confirmDeleteAll()`. Add `ConfirmDialog` component with `v-model:open="isDeleteDialogOpen"`. Pass `t('chat.deleteConfirmTitle')` as title, dynamic message with session count (`sessionList.length`), danger variant. Wire `@confirm` to call `deleteAllSessions()` with loading state on the confirm button. On success: close dialog + navigate. On error: keep dialog open, show inline error. Also replace `confirmDelete()` single-session flow with ConfirmDialog for consistency. **Files:** modify `frontend/src/views/ChatsView.vue` **Deliverable:** styled dialog replaces native confirm; shows session count; loading spinner on confirm button during API call; error allows retry. per Chat-D1 §Interaction Flow |
| P10.3 | Add missing i18n keys from Chat-D1 | Coder | 0.5h | — | draft | Verify and add any missing keys from Chat-D1 §i18n 键值: `chat.deleteConfirmTitle`, `chat.deleteConfirmMessage` (with `{{count}}`), `chat.confirmDelete`, `chat.cancelDelete`, `chat.deleteSuccess` (with `{{count}}`), `chat.deleteFailed`, `chat.onlyOneSession`. Check existing keys first to avoid duplicates. **Files:** `frontend/src/locales/en.json`, `frontend/src/locales/zh.json` **Deliverable:** all keys from D1 present in both locale files; `t('chat.deleteConfirmMessage', { count: 5 })` renders correctly. |
| P10.4 | Verify and close | Coder | 0.5h | P10.2, P10.3 | draft | Run `pnpm build` + `cargo test` + `pnpm test`. Manual smoke: (1) sessions exist → button visible → click → styled dialog with count → cancel → no change; (2) confirm → loading spinner → sessions cleared → new session → success toast; (3) 0 sessions → button hidden; (4) backend down → error message in dialog → retry works; (5) Escape closes dialog. **Deliverable:** all 5 scenarios pass; existing Chat-T22 tests still green. |

### Critical Path

```
P10.1 (ConfirmDialog.vue) → P10.2 (integrate in ChatsView) → P10.4 (verify)
P10.3 (i18n keys) ──────────────────────────────────────────→ P10.4 (verify)
```

Total estimated effort: **3.5h** (reduced from original 10h since core implementation is complete).

### Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|--------|------------|
| ConfirmDialog styles conflict with existing theme | Low | Low | Use CSS variables (`var(--af-*)`) consistent with project design system |
| Breaking existing `confirmDelete()` single-session flow | Medium | Medium | Test single-delete flow after refactor; keep fallback if ConfirmDialog doesn't fit |
| i18n key naming collision | Low | Low | Check existing `chat.*` keys before adding; reuse if already present |
| Chat-T22 regression | Low | Medium | Run full test suite before closing; Chat-T22 is verified and stable |

