| Frontend unit tests (5 tests) | `frontend/src/composables/__tests__/useSessions.spec.ts` | ✅ Verified | TC-T22.1 through TC-T22.8 |


The current UI uses `t('chat.deleteAllSessions')` (button title) and `t('chat.confirmDeleteAll')` (confirm dialog). Per Chat-D1 §i18n 键值, the design specifies 10 i18n keys. Need to verify and add missing keys to both locale files.


The current `confirm()` browser dialog is functional but Chat-D1 specifies using the existing `ConfirmDialog.vue` component for richer UX (session count display, styled buttons). This is a UX improvement, not a functional gap.

### Phase Breakdown — Remaining Work Only

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P10.1 | i18n: add missing chat deletion keys to en.json and zh.json | Coder | 0.5h | — | draft | Verify which keys already exist in `frontend/src/locales/en.json` and `frontend/src/locales/zh.json`. Add any missing keys from Chat-D1 §i18n 键值: `chat.deleteAll`, `chat.deleteAllSessions`, `chat.deleteConfirmTitle`, `chat.deleteConfirmMessage`, `chat.confirmDelete`, `chat.confirmDeleteAll`, `chat.deleteSuccess`, `chat.deleteFailed`, `chat.noSessionsToDelete`, `chat.onlyOneSession`, `chat.networkTimeout`. per Chat-D1 §i18n 键值. **Files:** `frontend/src/locales/en.json`, `frontend/src/locales/zh.json`. **Deliverable:** all referenced `t()` keys resolve in both languages; `pnpm build` succeeds. |
| P10.2 | (Optional) UX: replace browser `confirm()` with ConfirmDialog component | Coder | 1.5h | P10.1 | draft | Replace `confirm(t('chat.confirmDeleteAll'))` in ChatsView.vue `confirmDeleteAll()` with a proper dialog using existing ConfirmDialog component (if it exists) or a simple inline dialog. Show session count, styled confirm/cancel buttons, loading state during API call. per Chat-D1 §UI Component Structure. **Files:** `frontend/src/views/ChatsView.vue`, possibly `frontend/src/components/ConfirmDialog.vue`. **Deliverable:** delete-all shows custom dialog with session count; loading state disables confirm button; Escape/cancel closes dialog. |

### Risk Assessment

